race.comment: MARKET BLUE (1) scored two back then was always well back and could manage only a 6 length 7th at this track (23.28). Has ability and looks hard to stop. KRAKEN MILLY (2) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 4.5 lengths away in third (25.93) at this track in a Grade 5 over 450m. Racing well and deserves a win. NEENA BALE (3) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (25.33) last time in a Grade 5 at Sale. The form out of her last race has been franked. Leading chance. REIKO BENNY (7) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot most recently.
